Reasoning: The paper discusses the PAPR (Peak-to-Average Power Ratio) problem in OFDM (Orthogonal Frequency Division Multiplexing) transmission, which is a common issue in wireless communication systems. This problem is related to information theory (cs.IT), network infrastructure (cs.NI), and system engineering (cs.SY). Additionally, the paper proposes new directions for solving the problem using machine learning techniques (cs.MM) and optimization algorithms (cs.LG).
